    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Eustis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 6,
                                        1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Waller. If cruel treatment specified in your confidential August 30
                                was inflicted, how can French offer be accepted unreservedly?
                                Waller’s affidavit as to exact facts should be taken. If his
                                statements are accepted there, should be reasonable indemnity for
                                the cruel treatment. If disputed, would it not be satisfactory if
                                offer of immediate release were accepted with right on our part to
                                prove and claim damages for the cruel treatment above specified?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
